tool.name: PackCircleHierarchy

param.name: out_fc
param.dialogReference: The output feature class that will be created and to which the results will be written.
param.pythonReference: The output feature class that will be created and to which the results will be written.

param.name: value
param.dialogReference: Specifies the numeric field containing the attribute values that will be used to scale the proportional area of each. Null values are excluded from the calculations.
param.pythonReference: Specifies the numeric field containing the attribute values that will be used to scale the proportional area of each. Null values are excluded from the calculations.

param.name: group_field
param.dialogReference:
An attribute field from the input summary features that is used for grouping. Coordinates of features that have the same group field value will be averaged to determine the centroid of the packed circle features. The sum of numeric values within the group will determine the scaling of the proportional packed circle feature.

Suggested values might included administrative areas such as, neighborhoods, states/provinces, and countries.
param.pythonReference:
An attribute field from the input summary features that is used for grouping. Coordinates of features that have the same group field value will be averaged to determine the centroid of the packed circle features. The sum of numeric values within the group will determine the scaling of the proportional packed circle feature.

Suggested values might included administrative areas such as, neighborhoods, states/provinces, and countries.

param.name: case_field
param.dialogReference: The field in the input that will be used to aggregate data within geographic groupings. This field also determines hierarchical grouping of circles.
param.pythonReference: The field in the input that will be used to aggregate data within geographic groupings. This field also determines hierarchical grouping of circles.

param.name: category_field
param.dialogReference: The field in the input that will be used to calculate statistics separately for each unique attribute value. This field represents the lowest level of granularity within the data.
param.pythonReference: The field in the input that will be used to calculate statistics separately for each unique attribute value. This field represents the lowest level of granularity within the data.

param.name: diam_min
param.dialogReference:
A numerical constraint that will be used to determine the minimum proportional packed circle symbol diameter. The area of the packed circle will be scaled proportionally based on the aggregated data values within the group.

This measurement uses the units of the input feature coordinate system and may require some experimentation to achieve the desired effect.
param.pythonReference:
A numerical constraint that will be used to determine the maximum proportional packed circle symbol diameter. The area of the packed circle will be scaled proportionally based on the aggregated data values within the group.

This measurement uses the units of the input feature coordinate system and may require some experimentation to achieve the desired effect.

tool.summary: Geoprocessing tool for aggregating features into hierarchical packed circles on a map.
